    {
        "url": "/quotes/yamamoto_tsunetomo_536615",
        "quote": "Every day without fail one should consider himself as dead. There is a saying of the elders that goes, 'Step from under the eaves and you're a dead man. Leave the gate and the enemy is waiting.' This is not a matter of being careful. It is to consider oneself as dead beforehand.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Yamamoto Tsunetomo",
            "url": "/quotes/yamamoto_tsunetomo_536615"
